         <h3>Management Lab (ACCT-454-0)</h3>
         <p>This program helps students integrate concepts from their core courses and gain valuable consulting and field experience by tackling actual business problems and opportunities facing corporations and nonprofit firms in the Chicago area. In addition to attending weekly classes, students work directly with corporate and nonprofit institutions to understand, analyze and solve their problems in areas such as cost management, customer focus and response, benchmarking and new product development. Note: This course may not be dropped after the first week of the quarter.</p>
         <p>- Bala Balachandran</p>
       </div>
    </div>

