         <h3>Entrepreneurial Selling (KIEI-902-A)</h3>
         <p>This course will introduce you to the basics of selling and how you can use entrepreneurial techniques to make a difference in the success of your idea or inspire growth in your company. The class will focus on the fundamentals of sales and review the relationship of customer need identification and the reasons people buy. The course will help you develop your “entrepreneurial asking” skills to persuade your customers and business associates that your idea or solution will make the difference. You will master the six steps of selling as outlined in Ron Willingham’s book, Integrity Selling for the 21st Century. </p>
         <p>- Cheryl E. Mayberry McKissack</p>
       </div>
    </div>

